I've risked my job.
I could go to jail.

00:58:51.361 --> 00:58:54.531
$80,000 of that money
is mine.

00:58:57.909 --> 00:58:59.119
Look, just...

00:58:59.244 --> 00:59:01.913
let me have the key
to Sam's apartment.

00:59:01.997 --> 00:59:04.583
I'll get the address book
myself, OK?

00:59:30.484 --> 00:59:32.944
You god damn bastard!

00:59:33.028 --> 00:59:34.029
Why?

00:59:34.154 --> 00:59:36.573
Why? You were
my friend!

00:59:38.992 --> 00:59:41.328
I had a life,
god damn you.

00:59:41.495 --> 00:59:43.163
I had a life!

00:59:52.214 --> 00:59:55.467
Look, I don't even believe
in this stuff myself.

00:59:55.550 --> 00:59:57.010
But she was real.

00:59:57.135 --> 01:00:00.722
You think I'd come down here
if it wasn't real?

01:00:02.140 --> 01:00:02.724
You know,

01:00:03.183 --> 01:00:06.478
you told me if I had
any new information

01:00:06.561 --> 01:00:08.063
that I should come.

01:00:08.146 --> 01:00:09.481
So here I am.

01:00:13.652 --> 01:00:15.570
I know
how this sounds.

01:00:15.654 --> 01:00:17.572
I hear myself
saying it,

01:00:17.656 --> 01:00:19.574
and I want
to cringe.

01:00:19.658 --> 01:00:22.619
But this woman knew things
she couldn't have known.

01:00:22.702 --> 01:00:25.163
Things Sam
only said to me.

01:00:25.330 --> 01:00:28.333
OK, according to this
psychic lady,

01:00:28.458 --> 01:00:32.796
there are ghosts and spirits
all over the place

01:00:33.046 --> 01:00:34.798
watching us
all the time?

01:00:35.048 --> 01:00:35.799
Huh?

01:00:38.552 --> 01:00:41.513
Hell, I'm never going
to get undressed again.

01:00:41.555 --> 01:00:42.514
Excuse me.

01:00:42.556 --> 01:00:45.517
I got more
important things to do.

01:00:56.403 --> 01:00:58.697
The guy's name
is Willy Lopez.

01:00:58.822 --> 01:01:02.158
All I'm asking you to do
is check it out.

01:01:02.284 --> 01:01:03.618
OK. Wait here.

01:01:03.702 --> 01:01:07.414
Let me see if the guy's
got a record, all right?

01:01:07.539 --> 01:01:09.249
Great.

01:02:11.770 --> 01:02:13.313
What are you doing?

01:02:13.438 --> 01:02:15.440
Where's the file
on Willy Lopez?

01:02:15.565 --> 01:02:17.067
There isn't one.

01:02:17.150 --> 01:02:19.069
He was probably
some old boyfriend

01:02:19.152 --> 01:02:21.488
she was trying
to get even with.

01:02:21.571 --> 01:02:23.490
This psychic woman's
got a record

01:02:23.573 --> 01:02:26.076
that goes back
a long way.

01:02:26.201 --> 01:02:27.077
1 967,

01:02:27.202 --> 01:02:28.662
Shreveport,

01:02:28.787 --> 01:02:29.788
forgery...

01:02:30.121 --> 01:02:32.457
selling false I.D.

01:02:32.582 --> 01:02:35.210
Served one year, 1 9 7 1 .

01:02:35.335 --> 01:02:38.171
Baton Rouge,
arrested for fraud.

01:02:38.338 --> 01:02:42.384
Numbers racketeering,
served 1 0 months, 1 9 7 4.

01:02:42.509 --> 01:02:43.927
Look,
this is impossible.

01:02:44.177 --> 01:02:46.346
It goes on and on.

01:02:46.471 --> 01:02:48.348
She knew things,
private things.

01:02:48.473 --> 01:02:50.850
Now, how could she
have known all that?

01:02:50.976 --> 01:02:53.478
A lot of times
they read the obits.

01:02:53.520 --> 01:02:56.815
She just had to see
the word ''banker''--boom.

01:02:56.856 --> 01:02:59.317
Hell, they even go
through your...garbage

01:02:59.401 --> 01:03:01.403
to find things
they can use--

01:03:01.528 --> 01:03:02.862
letters, old papers.

01:03:03.113 --> 01:03:04.447
It doesn't take much.

01:03:05.532 --> 01:03:06.449
No.

01:03:08.660 --> 01:03:10.161
It was real.

01:03:12.872 --> 01:03:14.833
She knew about a...

01:03:15.166 --> 01:03:16.459
a sweater I knitted.

01:03:18.586 --> 01:03:19.879
And songs we sang.

01:03:24.884 --> 01:03:27.178
Our trip
to Montego Bay.

01:03:29.681 --> 01:03:30.724
I'm sorry.

01:03:30.890 --> 01:03:33.351
I know this is hard.

01:03:33.435 --> 01:03:35.770
People want so much
to believe.

01:03:35.895 --> 01:03:36.771
They're grieving,

01:03:36.896 --> 01:03:38.231
they're vulnerable...

01:03:39.566 --> 01:03:41.693
and they will
give anything

01:03:41.818 --> 01:03:43.319
for one last moment.

01:03:43.403 --> 01:03:44.738
Believe me.

01:03:44.863 --> 01:03:47.657
These people know
what they're doing.

01:03:47.741 --> 01:03:50.201
I know
how you must feel,

01:03:50.326 --> 01:03:53.246
but you know
you can press charges.

01:03:56.916 --> 01:03:57.917
No.

01:04:01.838 --> 01:04:02.756
Thank you.

01:04:17.437 --> 01:04:19.689
Oh, God,
let this be it.

01:04:32.452 --> 01:04:33.369
Yes.

01:04:43.963 --> 01:04:45.507
[Ring]

01:04:45.632 --> 01:04:46.591
Hello.

01:04:46.633 --> 01:04:47.967
Eddie? It's Carl Bruner.

01:04:48.259 --> 01:04:48.968
What's up?

01:04:49.260 --> 01:04:49.969
Everything's fine.

01:04:50.303 --> 01:04:51.596
Just, we're all set.

01:04:51.679 --> 01:04:54.557
Let me know what
you want me to do.

01:04:54.641 --> 01:04:56.559
Want you to
transfer the money

01:04:56.643 --> 01:04:57.977
from the 1 2
separate accounts

01:04:58.061 --> 01:04:59.104
into a single account
under the name Rita Miller.

01:05:00.522 --> 01:05:01.856
OK.

01:05:01.940 --> 01:05:03.858
Tomorrow at five minutes
before closing,

01:05:03.942 --> 01:05:05.777
3:55 p.m.,

01:05:05.860 --> 01:05:09.781
transfer the full account to
the First Island Bank of Nassau,

01:05:09.864 --> 01:05:12.575
registry number
486-9580.

01:05:12.700 --> 01:05:14.619
Call us when it's done.

01:05:14.702 --> 01:05:16.204
OK. I've got it.

01:05:16.287 --> 01:05:17.705
Just tell Mr. Balistrari

01:05:17.831 --> 01:05:20.625
that there won't be
any more problems, OK?

01:05:20.708 --> 01:05:22.210
Yeah. I'll do that.

01:05:22.293 --> 01:05:23.211
Thank you.

01:05:23.336 --> 01:05:24.629
Good work, Carl.

01:06:24.105 --> 01:06:26.608
Molly, why
can't you hear me?

01:06:26.691 --> 01:06:28.318
I need you.

01:06:29.611 --> 01:06:31.362
[Knock On Door]

01:06:32.906 --> 01:06:34.824
[Knock Knock Knock]

01:06:40.538 --> 01:06:41.873
Who is it?

01:06:41.915 --> 01:06:43.416
It's Carl, Molly.

01:06:43.541 --> 01:06:44.500
No.

01:06:44.626 --> 01:06:45.919
Don't open it,
Molly.

01:06:46.044 --> 01:06:47.545
He's a murderer.

01:06:47.629 --> 01:06:48.546
Hi.

01:06:48.630 --> 01:06:49.547
Hey.

01:06:49.631 --> 01:06:50.924
I know it's late.

01:06:51.049 --> 01:06:52.800
I'm sorry
to disturb you.

01:06:52.926 --> 01:06:55.470
I've been thinking
about you all day,

01:06:55.595 --> 01:06:58.890
and I feel really lousy
about what happened last night.

01:06:58.932 --> 01:07:00.308
This supernatural
thing just--

01:07:00.433 --> 01:07:02.477
Don't worry about it.
It's OK.

01:07:02.602 --> 01:07:03.728
No, it's not.

01:07:03.853 --> 01:07:06.773
You needed me to hear you,
and I didn't.

01:07:06.898 --> 01:07:09.776
I wasn't there for you,
and that was...

01:07:09.901 --> 01:07:11.527
that was wrong.

01:07:11.653 --> 01:07:12.946
It's just, I...

01:07:14.614 --> 01:07:15.949
I just--

01:07:16.032 --> 01:07:18.993
I want you to know
that I'm your friend.

01:07:19.077 --> 01:07:20.578
Thanks, Carl.

01:07:20.703 --> 01:07:22.538
You were never
our friend.

01:07:22.622 --> 01:07:24.958
That really means
a lot to me.

01:07:25.083 --> 01:07:27.710
Me, too. I brought you
some Japanese apple pears.

01:07:27.835 --> 01:07:29.337
I know you like them.

01:07:31.089 --> 01:07:31.965
Thanks.

01:07:32.090 --> 01:07:33.549
That's very sweet.

01:07:33.675 --> 01:07:35.843
Could I come in
for a second?

01:07:35.969 --> 01:07:38.388
It's just been
one of those days.

01:07:38.471 --> 01:07:39.639
Maybe some coffee?

01:07:39.806 --> 01:07:40.974
Yeah. Come on in.

01:07:41.140 --> 01:07:42.767
No, Molly.

01:07:42.892 --> 01:07:44.811
You seem a little tense.

01:07:44.894 --> 01:07:46.396
Are you OK?

01:07:46.479 --> 01:07:47.814
No. I'm fine.

01:07:47.939 --> 01:07:50.817
It's just--
What can I tell you?

01:07:50.942 --> 01:07:52.443
It's been tough.

01:07:52.485 --> 01:07:54.737
It just still hurts
so much.

01:07:54.821 --> 01:07:56.155
You lying snake.

01:07:56.239 --> 01:07:59.117
And on top of it,
it's stuff at work.

01:07:59.367 --> 01:08:01.452
They've given me
my own accounts,

01:08:01.577 --> 01:08:02.870
which is good,

01:08:02.996 --> 01:08:06.457
but I just haven't really
had time to adjust,

01:08:06.582 --> 01:08:08.376
kind of absorb
everything.

01:08:12.672 --> 01:08:13.923
It's no big deal.

01:08:16.926 --> 01:08:17.844
Yeah.

01:08:24.183 --> 01:08:27.145
Can I have just
a little more cream?

01:08:28.187 --> 01:08:29.397
Yeah.

01:08:30.815 --> 01:08:31.858
Oh, shit.

01:08:32.025 --> 01:08:34.485
Jesus. I can't believe
I did that.

01:08:34.569 --> 01:08:35.778
Are you all right?

01:08:35.862 --> 01:08:37.822
Yeah, I'm fine.

01:08:37.864 --> 01:08:38.781
Oh, God.

01:08:38.865 --> 01:08:41.159
Let me throw that
in the washer.

01:08:41.242 --> 01:08:44.037
Don't worry about it.
It's OK. It's just...

01:08:44.203 --> 01:08:45.663
You want
another shirt?

01:08:45.747 --> 01:08:48.207
No. It'll dry.
It'll just take a minute.

01:08:48.291 --> 01:08:49.751
There you go.

01:08:53.004 --> 01:08:54.255
Where were you today?

01:08:54.547 --> 01:08:57.550
I thought you were going
to come into the bank

01:08:57.675 --> 01:08:59.010
and sign those papers?

01:08:59.093 --> 01:09:01.763
I was supposed to,
but I didn't have time.

01:09:01.888 --> 01:09:04.849
I went to the police.

01:09:11.230 --> 01:09:12.190
You did?

01:09:12.523 --> 01:09:14.400
Wow. What
did you tell them?

01:09:14.525 --> 01:09:15.818
What did they say?

01:09:15.902 --> 01:09:17.403
It was awful.

01:09:18.738 --> 01:09:20.615
I felt really stupid.

01:09:20.740 --> 01:09:24.035
They brought out a file
on this woman and--

01:09:24.077 --> 01:09:26.037
At least
1 0 inches thick.

01:09:27.163 --> 01:09:28.748
A ripoff artist, huh?

01:09:28.873 --> 01:09:29.916
No, Molly.

01:09:31.751 --> 01:09:33.628
You know,
the sad thing...

01:09:35.254 --> 01:09:37.215
is that
I believed her.

01:09:37.298 --> 01:09:38.758
Molly...

01:09:40.843 --> 01:09:42.887
sometimes
we need to believe.

01:09:44.514 --> 01:09:45.848
Why? What's the point?

01:09:45.932 --> 01:09:47.308
Molly, it's not easy to face
the realities of life sometimes.

01:09:49.769 --> 01:09:51.813
You got to
give yourself that.

01:09:51.938 --> 01:09:56.651
What you've got to remember
is the love that you guys felt.

01:09:56.776 --> 01:09:59.112
You got to remember
how good Sam was.

01:09:59.153 --> 01:10:01.656
You were everything
to him, Molly.

01:10:01.781 --> 01:10:03.116
You were his life.

01:10:17.880 --> 01:10:19.215
I feel so alone.

01:10:27.932 --> 01:10:29.267
You're not alone.

01:10:29.350 --> 01:10:30.268
OK?

01:10:31.644 --> 01:10:34.021
You got your work.
You're incredibly talented.

01:10:34.147 --> 01:10:35.064
You're young.

01:10:35.148 --> 01:10:37.358
You're fantastically
gorgeous.

01:10:39.068 --> 01:10:41.404
I don't know
what's real anymore.

01:10:42.655 --> 01:10:45.158
I don't know
what to think.

01:10:48.369 --> 01:10:50.079
Just think about Sam.

01:10:52.748 --> 01:10:55.626
Think about the time
you guys had together.

01:10:56.836 --> 01:10:58.671
How wonderful that was.

01:10:59.922 --> 01:11:01.048
Yeah.

01:11:02.258 --> 01:11:05.178
Let your feelings out,
Moll. It's OK.

01:11:05.344 --> 01:11:07.763
Life turns on a dime.

01:11:09.265 --> 01:11:10.266
You know?

01:11:11.976 --> 01:11:12.977
I mean...

01:11:14.103 --> 01:11:15.646
people think that...

01:11:15.771 --> 01:11:18.816
they're there forever, that there's
always going to be tomorrow,

01:11:18.941 --> 01:11:20.234
but that's bullshit.

01:11:20.359 --> 01:11:22.320
Sam taught us that.

01:11:23.821 --> 01:11:26.157
You have to
live for now.

01:11:28.784 --> 01:11:29.911
For today.

01:11:50.014 --> 01:11:50.890
I can't.

01:11:51.015 --> 01:11:51.891
I'm sorry.

01:11:52.016 --> 01:11:52.892
It's OK.

01:11:53.059 --> 01:11:55.728
I--I--I can't.
It's just too soon.

01:11:55.811 --> 01:11:56.729
It's OK.

01:11:56.812 --> 01:11:58.731
You've been great,
Carl.

01:12:01.734 --> 01:12:03.694
But I need you
to leave.

01:12:03.736 --> 01:12:05.071
I understand totally.

01:12:05.196 --> 01:12:06.072
Please.

01:12:11.786 --> 01:12:14.997
Could we just have dinner
tomorrow night? Just talk?

01:12:15.081 --> 01:12:17.416
Can I interest you
in that?

01:12:18.793 --> 01:12:19.835
Yeah.

01:12:19.919 --> 01:12:20.836
Sure.

01:12:20.920 --> 01:12:21.837
Great.

